#The following are steps required for provisioning a web server using azure virtual machine.
- Select a subscription
- Choose a resource group
- Name your virtual machine
- Choose a region
- Select an Availability Option
- Choose an image
- Select Virtual Size
- Configure Administrator Account
- Configure Inbound port rules
- Select OS disk type
- Disable boot diagnostics
- Name tag and value
- Review and Create your virtual machine
- Connect into your VM using RDP connection
- Install web server features using powershell cli
- Test your connection using your public IP address
- Configure web server files located at "C: /inetpub/wwwroot/" in Windows 2019 DataCenter G2 Server
